<h2>Resource Loader</h2>
<p>
    Technical implementation of the <a href="/intents/loader/">Loader Intent</a>. Provides composable traits that
    any loading consumer — <a href="/blocks/router/">Router</a>, forms, data grids, infinite scroll — can use to
    apply the correct loading UX based on the application's declared intent profile.
</p>
<p>
    Implemented as a <strong>Virtual Element</strong> using comment-based markers, ensuring no extra
    <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrappers pollute parent-child layout relationships (Grid/Flex).
    Part of the <a href="/projects/webresources/">Web Resources</a> ecosystem.
</p>

<h3>Web Standards Alignment</h3>
